# fit the image

Suppose we have following image of ratio `1:4`

<img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox='0 0 320 80' xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%3E%3Cstyle%3E .text %7B font: 60px sans-serif; fill: %23fff; %7D %3C/style%3E%3Crect width='100%25' height='100%25' fill='%23f44336' /%3E%3Ctext x='50' y='60' class='text'%3EBFE.dev%3C/text%3E%3C/svg%3E" width="600">

Now in an HTML structure like below, please fit the image to the container div, just as if it is used as container's background-image with `background-size:cover`.

```html
<div>
  <img class="image" src="..." />
</div>
```

1. 50x50

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="50" >

2. 100x100

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="100" >

3. 200x100

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="200" >

4. 100x200

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="100" >

5. 300x100

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="300" >

6. 100x300

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="100" >

7. 700x100

<img src="data:image/png;base64," width="700" >

[Problem Link](https://bigfrontend.dev/css/fit-the-image)

```css
.image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}
```
